raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: pymssql
  version: "2.3.13"

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/${{ name }}-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2137e904b1a65546be4ccb96730a391fcd5a85aab8a0632721feb5d7e39cfbce
  patches:
    - patches/0001-customize-compiler.patch

build:
  number: 0
  script:
    - if: unix
      then:
        - export LINK_FREETDS_STATICALLY=NO
        - python setup.py build_ext --include-dirs=$PREFIX/include --library-dirs=$PREFIX/lib
    - if: win
      then:
        - set LINK_FREETDS_STATICALLY=NO
        - python setup.py build_ext --include-dirs=%PREFIX%\include --library-dirs=%PREFIX%\lib
    - python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - cython >=3.1.0
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
    - ${{ compiler('cxx') }}
  host:
    - python
    - cython >=3.1.0
    - freetds
    - packaging >=24.2
    - pip
    - setuptools >=80.0
    - setuptools-git
    - setuptools_scm >=8.0
    - toml
    - wheel >=0.36.2
    # seems to work without standard-distuitils
    # - standard-distutils
  run:
    - python
    - freetds

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - pymssql
      pip_check: true

about:
  license: LGPL-2.1-or-later
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: DB-API interface to Microsoft SQL Server for Python. (new Cython-based version)
  homepage: http://pymssql.org
  repository: https://github.com/pymssql/pymssql
  documentation: https://pymssql.readthedocs.io/en/stable/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - primozgodec
    - mariusvniekerk
    - xylar
